    "summary": "After being educated as Industrial designer at the Delft University of Technology I have been active as professional design consultant for almost two decades. As co-founder of Landmark Design Holding and as founder of Landmark Switzerland I received national and international recognition.  I was active as board member in designers' association in the Netherlands (KIO/BNO), in Europe (BEDA) and at global level (ICSID).  I gained academic experience in the Netherlands and was professor of Industrial Design at KAIST in South Korea. In 2006 I was appointed by the Ministry of Economic Affairs to set up the Netherlands Office for Science & Technology (NOST) at the Netherlands Embassy in New Delhi India (2006-'12)and in Brazil (2012-2014). Until march 2015 I worked for the Ministry of Economic Affairs as counsellor in The Hague. Since 2015 I am offering my expertise as independent senior consultant for companies, research organization and knowledge institutes on matters related to International Innovation and international collaboration, with strong focus India. I was appointed special envoy for India by HSD, the Hague Security Delta. I am also the Dutch representative of TERI, The Energy and Resources Institute with headquarters in New Delhi, and mentor for product development at the Hogeschool van Amsterdam.\n\nSpecialties: Professional: Design & Innovation methodologies; design of public services & products, medical products, concept development. Consultancy in Science & Technology & Innovation\n\nPersonal: Design Thinking & Out-of-the-Box thinking, creating opportunities, connecting people & ideas, initiating projects & collaborations, positive thinking.\n\nExperience: B2B in advanced & emerging economies, match-making, higher education, counseling\nLanguages: Dutch, English and German and French conversational level.",
